> Hello Type 2 List:
>
> I just pulled the engine, got the firewall off
> to clean my gas tank which I am suspicious of....
>
> Well, all ok so far but I was stymied by the 13mm bolts
> holding the metal bands that go over the tank--they are frozen
> big time.  I was twisting them, heard some nasty sounds up above
> and then finally realized I was twisting up the band itself!
> I put a couple of turns in it before I stopped.
>
> There doesnt seem to be any way to lock the tops of these bolts down.

I put a vice grip on them and let it but up against the tank
Lube the bolt with some spray lube of some sort, 2 turns off 1 turn on
repeat etc.
This usually keeps the bolt from breaking too.
Don"t cut them unless you want to weld new ones in

> I cannot seem to unfreeze them and am way too chicken to use a torch
> in that area.  It seems hard to getliquid wrench on an upside down bolt.
>
> I am tempted to just cut them and replace them with some metal webbing.
> Is this a bad idea?  It might very well be a bad
> idea as I have no concept at all
> how they attach on the other side.
>
> Any other suggestions?
>
> Thanks!
>
